<br>
Now, personally I couldn't honestly say if there was a change, but if I remember I had to run through freeport to the boat and didn't see anything different myself..<br>
<br>
I think you may be encountering the fact that there is a change to feign death in mobs of level 32 and up. When I first experienced it first hand, it was a bit disconcerting to me as well..  Mobs of level 32 and up do not have the mem blur component of feign death, IE you are not removed from their hate list... There is a chance of it, and with static spawn mobs (which the ones you listed are not) they will forget you when they return to their spawn points. (although it seems like this is not always the case with mobs of level 40+). You might also eventually find that mobs of level 50+ will not buy your FD if you've done damage to them..<br>
<br>
But your mobs you listed are definitely the ones you're likely to pass by in Permafrost where you would see this kind of FD deal, and if your monk is 24 or something like that, it's likely you got Tundra Jack as Brandl passed agro on to him. Guk might also be a spot where a FD class might first encounter mobs of the level range to first see this behavior as well. For me, I first saw it hunting frogs and dogs in Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
But don't worry, you get used to it.. Actually kinda useful in the right situations for splitting pulls. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/ugwynetwoodsister.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gwynet Woodsister</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Druzzil Ro Member</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(6/7/01 4:15:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Anyone else having problems with FD since the 5th?</span><hr size=1> The only problem I have with FD is that now in 6 hours of pulling in Hate I get about 25 times the message &quot;Leorny has fallen to the ground&quot;. My skill is at 188.<br>
